{"page":1,"prev_page_endpoint":null,"next_page_endpoint":null,"total_pages":1,"reasons":[{"created_at":"2014-05-23T00:07:19Z","content":"Everyone deserves a fair trial! This case is ridiculous. The judge summarily discarded Dr. Rancourt\u2019s main defence without any valid justification. Please sign this petition demanding that the trial start again with a judge that has no ties to the University of Ottawa. uOttawa fired Dr. Rancourt and is sponsoring a defamation lawsuit against him. Clearly, a judge for this trial must not have any ties to uOttawa to avoid a conflict of interest. Thanks for signing!","like_count":1,"author_name":"Julie Catalyst","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/8227194"},{"created_at":"2014-05-28T16:07:18Z","content":"I am a graduate of the University of Ottawa and it's shameful that my alma mater is engaging in practices like this. ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Alex Del Duca","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/102222320"},{"created_at":"2014-05-23T00:06:42Z","content":"My family and I have been adversely affected by corruption and bias in the Canadian legal system, and I feel it is my duty to do what I can to improve this system.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Pierre Pontbriand","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/89691067"},{"created_at":"2014-05-23T11:51:54Z","content":"The judges and the legal profession in general are out of control and have become unaccountable to the people of Canada.  The people of Canada are losing respect for the Administration of Justice in Canada.  It is time for change.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Vernon Beck","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/16563815"},{"created_at":"2014-05-22T21:42:46Z","content":"There are several aspects of this case that are troubling. One is that the case is being financed by the University of Ottawa, with a promise to share the benefits if it is successful. I feel that as such it is being used as a SLAPP against Mr. Rancourt. This has serious implications for all dissenters and whistleblowers in Canada. In addition, I feel that the justices involved in this case have brought the legal profession into disrepute by their conduct in the courtroom (at times abusive and occasionally out of control, according to reports I have heard). The conflict of interest issue is an aspect of this. It seems odd that another judge, without ties, could not be found. Surely they must exist? ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Ian Bron","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/62786033"},{"created_at":"2014-05-29T21:54:18Z","content":" If you need an example of a clear conflict of interest in a court proceeding (judge and plaintiff), this is a classic. This is important to anyone who expects judicial fairness.","like_count":1,"author_name":"Greg Byers","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/42685446"},{"created_at":"2014-05-30T01:10:56Z","content":"I am a graduate of University of Ottawa; I cannot believe that the plaintiff is receiving her legal costs paid for by the university to sue a former professor of the same university! Nor can I believe the judge in this case has direct ties to the university of Ottawa as an graduate and other obvious bais. Wow. As an Ontarian this feels like a banana republic.  ","like_count":1,"author_name":"Nancy McColl","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/102981290"},{"created_at":"2014-05-22T01:33:19Z","content":"A public institution with bottomless pockets funding a lawsuit against a self-represented wrongly dismissed former employee all judged by a man with financial connections to the same institution.......What a sham! Good for you Denis for walking out!","like_count":1,"author_name":"David Mandelzys","author_url":"http://api.change.org/u/23776212"},{"created_at":"2014-05-29T08:51:37Z","content":"Time to kick insidious race hate out of our hallowed halls of learning... Skin color or the lack thereof cannot be a cover for insalubrious shenanigans, petty, ignorant social politics and this entrenched preVictorian ideology miasma 